      <div type="printedheader">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_4618_p1"> <seg type="com">
                        <note type="addendum" xml:id="K_4618_c0">Nachträglicher Stempel oben rechts mit von dritter Hand eingetragener Nummer:
          <bibl>Gotthardbahn | <date when="1872-05-13">13 MAI 1872</date>. | <choice>
                                    <abbr>N<hi rend="sup">o</hi> </abbr>
                                    <expan>Numero (Nummer)</expan>
                                </choice> 1854.</bibl>
          – Nachträgliche Inhaltsangabe oben links von dritter Hand: <bibl>Angebot auf Ausführung des <choice>
                                    <abbr>gr.</abbr>
                                    <expan>gross / groß</expan>
                                </choice> <placeName type="place" key="Alpen">Alpen</placeName>tunnels | I <choice>
                                    <abbr>Depart.</abbr>
                                    <expan>Departement</expan>
                                </choice> </bibl>
          – Nachträgliche Notiz unten links von dritter Hand: <bibl>
                                <choice>
                                    <abbr>Prot.</abbr>
                                    <expan>Protokoll</expan>
                                </choice> <date when="1872-05-22">22 V. 72</date>. <choice>
                                    <abbr>N.</abbr>
                                    <expan>Nummer</expan>
                                </choice> 385.</bibl> </note>
                    </seg> <lb xml:id="p1-l1"/>
          <fw>
            <persName type="person" key="Tompkins Charles H.">C. H. TOMPKINS</persName>, <choice>
                            <abbr>PRES'T</abbr>
                            <expan>PRESIDENT (Präsident)</expan>
                        </choice> </fw>
        </p>
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_4618_p2">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l2"/>
          <fw>
                        <persName type="person" key="Reynolds William H.">WM.H. REYNOLDS</persName>, <choice>
                            <abbr>TREAS.</abbr>
                            <expan>TREASURER (Kassier)</expan>
                        </choice> </fw>
        </p>
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_4618_p3">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l3"/>
          <fw>OFFICE OF THE<lb xml:id="p1-l4"/>
		<placeName type="place" key="Vereinigte Staaten von Amerika">American</placeName> Diamond Drill <choice>
                            <abbr>Co.</abbr>
                            <expan>Compagnia / Compagnie / Company (Gesellschaft)</expan>
                        </choice>,<lb xml:id="p1-l5"/>
            Manufacturers of <persName type="person" key="Leschot Rodolphe">LESCHOT'S</persName> PATENT<lb xml:id="p1-l6"/>
		DIAMOND-POINTED STEAM DRILLS,<lb xml:id="p1-l7"/>
		For Mining, Quarrying, Shafting, Tunneling, Prospecting, Draining, Grading, and Submarine Blasting.<lb xml:id="p1-l8"/>

		SPECIAL ATTENTION GIVEN TO DEEP BORING FOR TESTING THE VALUE OF MINES AND QUARRIES.<lb xml:id="p1-l9"/>

		61 LIBERTY STREET,</fw>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="dateline">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_4618_p4">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l10"/>
          <del>
            <fw>New York</fw>
                    </del>, <placeName type="place" key="Paris (F)">Paris</placeName> <date when="1872-05-11"> May 11 <fw>187</fw>2
</date> </p>
      </div>
      <div type="address">
        <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_4618_p5">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l11"/>
          <choice>
                        <abbr>Dr</abbr>
                        <expan>Doktor / Doctor</expan>
                    </choice> A. Escher <choice>
                        <abbr>Prest</abbr>
                        <expan>President (Präsident)</expan>
                    </choice> <supplied>
                        <choice>
                            <abbr>etc.</abbr>
                            <expan>et cetera (und anderes)</expan>
                        </choice> </supplied>
                    <note type="transcript">wohl das sog. tironische Et und c. als Zeichen für etc.</note> <placeName type="place" key="Luzern (Stadt)">Lucerne</placeName> </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_4618_p6">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l12"/>
		My dear Sir</p>
      </div>
    </front>
    <body>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_4618_p7">
                <lb xml:id="p1-l13"/>
		Can the time for the<lb xml:id="p1-l14"/>
		opening of the bids for contracts offered to your<lb xml:id="p1-l15"/>
		company, be extended for twenty or thirty days?<lb xml:id="p1-l16"/>
		I am authorized to enter into competition with<lb xml:id="p1-l17"/>
		others, but am waiting for one or two items of in<lb break="no" xml:id="p1-l18"/>formation  
		that will enable me to place our<lb xml:id="p1-l19"/>
		Company among the bidders for the work. I trust<lb xml:id="p1-l20"/>
		that the <date when="1872-05-18">18<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of May</date>, may not be arbitrarily fixed<lb xml:id="p1-l21"/>
		as we are very anxious that an <placeName type="place" key="Vereinigte Staaten von Amerika">American</placeName> Asso<lb break="no" xml:id="p1-l22"/>ciation  
		may help in the Grand fulfillment of<lb xml:id="p1-l23"/>
		Your Company's design. Our Machinery is now<lb xml:id="p1-l24"/>
		so perfect, that we feel confident that we can<lb xml:id="p1-l25"/>
		work with greater dispatch and economy, than<lb xml:id="p1-l26"/>
		can be secured by any other system or organiza<lb break="no" xml:id="p1-l27"/>tion.  
		Please favor me with an early reply.</p>
      <p rend="left" xml:id="K_4618_p8">
                <lb xml:id="p1-l28"/>
		I send you pamphlet of<lb xml:id="p1-l29"/>
		our Drills.
		</p>
    </body>
    <back>
      <div type="closer">
                <p rend="right" xml:id="K_4618_p9">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l30"/>
		Respectfully</p>
            </div>
     <div type="address">
                <p rend="right" xml:id="K_4618_p10">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l31"/>
		A. D. Munsen</p>
            </div>
